mod.rs
     1вҶ’//! Structured logging.
     2вҶ’//!
     3вҶ’//! Add the `kv` feature to your `Cargo.toml` to enable
     4вҶ’//! this module:
     5вҶ’//!
     6вҶ’//! ```toml
     7вҶ’//! [dependencies.log]
     8вҶ’//! features = ["kv"]
     9вҶ’//! ```
    10вҶ’//!
    11вҶ’//! # Structured logging in `log`
    12вҶ’//!
    13вҶ’//! Structured logging enhances traditional text-based log records with user-defined
    14вҶ’//! attributes. Structured logs can be analyzed using a variety of data processing
    15вҶ’//! techniques, without needing to find and parse attributes from unstructured text first.
    16вҶ’//!
    17вҶ’//! In `log`, user-defined attributes are part of a [`Source`] on the log record.
    18вҶ’//! Each attribute is a key-value; a pair of [`Key`] and [`Value`]. Keys are strings
    19вҶ’//! and values are a datum of any type that can be formatted or serialized. Simple types
    20вҶ’//! like strings, booleans, and numbers are supported, as well as arbitrarily complex
    21вҶ’//! structures involving nested objects and sequences.
    22вҶ’//!
    23вҶ’//! ## Adding key-values to log records
    24вҶ’//!
    25вҶ’//! Key-values appear before the message format in the `log!` macros:
    26вҶ’//!
    27вҶ’//! ```
    28вҶ’//! # use log::info;
    29вҶ’//! info!(a = 1; "Something of interest");
    30вҶ’//! ```
    31вҶ’//!
    32вҶ’//! Key-values support the same shorthand identifier syntax as `format_args`:
    33вҶ’//!
    34вҶ’//! ```
    35вҶ’//! # use log::info;
    36вҶ’//! let a = 1;
    37вҶ’//!
    38вҶ’//! info!(a; "Something of interest");
    39вҶ’//! ```
    40вҶ’//!
    41вҶ’//! Values are capturing using the [`ToValue`] trait by default. To capture a value
    42вҶ’//! using a different trait implementation, use a modifier after its key. Here's how
    43вҶ’//! the same example can capture `a` using its `Debug` implementation instead:
    44вҶ’//!
    45вҶ’//! ```
    46вҶ’//! # use log::info;
    47вҶ’//! info!(a:? = 1; "Something of interest");
    48вҶ’//! ```
    49вҶ’//!
    50вҶ’//! The following capturing modifiers are supported:
    51вҶ’//!
    52вҶ’//! - `:?` will capture the value using `Debug`.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
